description: Renew an existing watch for seven days. The state of the watch after renewal is `ACTIVE`, and the `expire_time` is seven days from the renewal. Renewing a watch in an error state (e.g. `SUSPENDED`) succeeds if the error is no longer present, but fail otherwise. After a watch has expired, RenewWatch returns `NOT_FOUND`.

schema.description: OAuth 2 access token. Most APIs require `https://www.googleapis.com/auth/forms` scope. Google Auth / Service Account Token can be used to obtain a valid access token.
API key can be generated in Google Developer Console in APIs & Services section. Leave blank if OAuth access token is used.
Selector specifying which fields to include in a partial response.
Required. The ID of the Form.
Required. The ID of the Watch to renew.
